page.title: 14LANDSCAPE,BUILDINGS 03800597
page.content: This is an upland rural area, within the{National Park,}where all buildings must conform to N.P. specifications. Most are of natural grey sandstone with slate roofs.{Domestic property } consists of 1 or 2 storeyed farmhouses or tenants' cottages which usually have small 4 paned windows. Many have had porches added recently. Most farms have some original outbuildings with 1 or 2 steel_framed modern sheds attached.{Rochester village}is mainly 1 row of terraced houses built in the mid_19th century. Gardens and coal houses are across the road. There is a village hall,garage,filling_station, snack bar and post office.The{Georgian {style}Presbyterian church and manse were built in 1826.The{council houses} are of the Swedish Airey type.there are{2 16th century bastles.The army {camp}has prefabricated wooden billets.
